---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../../components/PageHeader.astro";
import SectionCard from "../../components/SectionCard.astro";

const logo = "<(.____.)>";
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Programming — ${logo}`}
  description="C++, Computer Science, algorithms, tools, and engineering practice."
  lang="en"
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Programming"
    description="Modern C++, STL, algorithms, data structures, Computer Science, development tools, and practical projects."
  />

  <section class="intro">
    <p>
      My main practical goal is to become a strong software developer. That
      requires more than knowing syntax. It means understanding the language,
      algorithms, architecture, tools, testing, debugging, and real engineering
      trade-offs.
    </p>

    <p>
      My current main language is C++. Through it, I study low-level details,
      resource management, performance, data structures, and the development of
      more complex software systems.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="grid">
    <SectionCard
      title="C++"
      description="Modern C++, RAII, Rule of Zero/Three/Five, move semantics, templates, smart pointers, error handling, and architecture."
      href="/en/programming/cpp/"
    />

    <SectionCard
      title="STL"
      description="Containers, iterators, algorithms, ranges, strings, map/set, unordered containers, and standard idioms."
      href="/en/programming/stl/"
    />

    <SectionCard
      title="Algorithms and Data Structures"
      description="Sorting, graphs, dynamic programming, trees, hash tables, heaps, strings, and basic algorithmic culture."
      href="/en/programming/algorithms/"
    />

    <SectionCard
      title="Computer Science"
      description="Operating systems, networks, compilers, databases, computer architecture, and fundamental ideas."
      href="/en/programming/cs/"
    />

    <SectionCard
      title="Tools"
      description="Git, CMake, compilers, debuggers, profilers, testing, CI, and the developer workflow."
      href="/en/programming/tools/"
    />

    <SectionCard
      title="Projects"
      description="Mini-projects, game prototypes, tools, learning experiments, and everything that turns theory into code."
      href="/en/projects/"
    />
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Planned materials</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>How I am building my modern C++ foundation</li>
      <li>What to know about the STL</li>
      <li>Mini-projects for improving at C++</li>
      <li>How to set up a C++ workflow</li>
      <li>What I learned about RAII</li>
      <li>Why algorithms still matter</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <style>
    .intro {
      margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    }

    .grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
      gap: var(--space-md);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>